# 1. AWS Global Infrastructure

AWS infrastructure is globally distributed to provide high availability.

```mermaid
graph TD
AWS_Global_Network --> Regions
Regions --> Availability_Zones
Availability_Zones --> Data_Centers
Data_Centers --> Physical_Servers
Physical_Servers --> Virtual_Machines
```

### Why this exists

Traditional hosting had:

- single datacenter failures
- scaling limits
- regional outages

AWS solved this using distributed infrastructure.

---

# 2. Regions and Availability Zones

```mermaid
graph TD
Region --> AZ1
Region --> AZ2
Region --> AZ3
AZ1 --> DataCenter1
AZ1 --> DataCenter2
```

Benefits:

- fault isolation
- high availability
- disaster recovery

Applications should run across multiple AZs.

