# 5. Virtual Private Cloud (VPC)

A VPC is a logically isolated network.

```mermaid
graph TD
AWS_Region --> VPC
VPC --> Public_Subnet
VPC --> Private_Subnet
```

Purpose:

- network isolation
- IP address control
- routing configuration
- security policies

---

# 6. Subnets

Subnets divide a VPC network.

```mermaid
graph TD
VPC --> Public_Subnet
VPC --> Private_Subnet

Public_Subnet --> Load_Balancer
Private_Subnet --> Database
```

Typical architecture:

| Layer | Components |
|------|-------------|
| Public | Load balancer |
| App | EC2 |
| Data | Database |

---

# 7. Internet Gateway

Internet access requires an Internet Gateway.

```mermaid
graph TD
User --> Internet
Internet --> Internet_Gateway
Internet_Gateway --> Route_Table
Route_Table --> Public_Subnet
```

Without an IGW, instances cannot access the internet.

---

# 8. NAT Gateway

Private instances use NAT Gateway for outbound access.

```mermaid
graph TD
Private_EC2 --> Route_Table
Route_Table --> NAT_Gateway
NAT_Gateway --> Internet_Gateway
Internet_Gateway --> Internet
```

Purpose:

- outbound internet access
- no inbound traffic allowed

---

# 9. Security Layers

AWS provides two network security layers.

## Security Groups

Instance firewall.

```mermaid
graph TD
Internet --> Security_Group
Security_Group --> EC2
```

Characteristics:

- stateful
- instance level

---

## Network ACL

Subnet firewall.

```mermaid
graph TD
Internet --> Network_ACL
Network_ACL --> Subnet
```

Characteristics:

- stateless
- subnet boundary protection

---

